observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
 Municipal General Services Officer to:
a. Prepare and submit the PPE Ledger Card (PPELC) and PPE lapsing schedules with complete details to provide accurate and reliable PPE account balances, pursuant to IPSAS 1 and 17, Section 114 of the MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I and Sections 111 and 112 of PD No. 1445;
b. Record the transfer of PPE amounting to P461,884.00 from the Trust Fund to the General Fund, properly compute for the depreciation of each item pursuant to Section 104 of the MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I and Philippine Application Guidance (PAG) 3 of IPSAS 17 and submit the copies of the JEV with supporting documents to the Audit Team;
c. Analyze the accounting entries made in recording of completed projects pertaining to land improvements and buildings and other structures and make the necessary adjustments in the books of accounts, also provide the copies of the JEV to the Audit Team;
 Municipal Accountant to:
d. Provide to the Audit Team the basis for using Zonal Value in revaluing the balances of the Municipality’s owned lands, together with the reference used in the computation of the zonal value, otherwise, reverse JEV No. 100-2023-12-2266 dated December 31, 2023, the entry made by the Municipal Accountant for the recognition of Gain on Asset Valuation to Market Value of Lands amounting to P131,815,625.49;
e. Submit a written Assessor’s Office prepared a new supporting list of land owned by the Municipality; and
f. Submit to the Audit Team the proof of ownership of each Land owned by the Municipality, including but not limited to, Transfer Certificate of Title, Deed of Donation and Deed of Sale, to verify the accuracy, reliability and completeness of the 471 Land items reported as owned by the Municipality as of December 31, 2023.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the Municipal Accountant and other concerned officers and employees to:
a. Strictly implement all the pertinent provisions of COA Circular No. 97-002 on the grant, utilization and liquidation of cash advances and ensure that the disbursing officer is properly bonded in accordance with Treasury TC No. 002-2019, otherwise, appoint or designate this Disbursing Officer (DO) for the grant of additional cash advances;
b. Stop the practice of paying regular telephone expenses, such as rentals, subscriptions, light and water, etc. through cash advances and directly pay the suppliers by issuance of checks;
c. Submit the lacking supporting documents such as (a) Certification from the Chief Accountant that the previous cash advances have been fully liquidated and accounted for in the books, (b) approved payroll of list of payees indicating their net pay and (c) Accomplishment Reports; and
d. Immediately liquidate the outstanding cash advances relative to the Intelligence and Confidential/Intelligence Fund pursuant to Section 6.2.2 of the COA-DBM-DILG-GCG-DND JC No. 2015-01 dated January 8, 2015.
